Privacy Policy
I. GENERAL PROVISIONS
We kindly request that you thoroughly read this privacy statement. It provides important information about how your personal data may be handled. When you use the app, you confirm that you have read, understood, and agreed to these terms. By accessing or using the app, you consent to the processing of your personal data in accordance with this privacy statement.
At
Ozuna Limited
(referred to as "our company," "we," or "us"), we prioritize your privacy. This Privacy Statement ("Privacy Statement") outlines our commitment to safeguarding your data and delineates the kinds of information we may collect when you utilize one or more of our mobile applications (referred to as "the App" or "our App"). It also explains how we, along with some of the companies we collaborate with, process this information.
When we mention personal data (or personal information), we are referring to any information that can be used to identify a natural person, either directly or indirectly. This could be through an identification number or through one or more factors related to their physical, physiological, mental, economic, cultural, or social status.
This Privacy Statement is applicable to all users and others who access the App (referred to as "Users"). As per the GDPR, we function as the data controller.
II. INFORMATION COLLECTION
Information is collected from or about you from various sources, as described below.
2.1 Data You Provide
When you interact with our App, we request and gather specific personal details about you. This information is essential for the proper execution of the agreement between us. Without this data, we cannot offer full functionality of the App or deliver the services you require.
Personal Details: This is the information you voluntarily provide when the App is set up to track your data, store your records, and/or manage them for convenience and at your explicit request.
Registration and/or Account Details: To create an account, we need certain data like your email address, Facebook ID, or Google ID – the requirement depends on the App's configuration.
Content Details: This includes photos, images, videos, audio files, documents, and other data that you upload via the App.
2.2 Automatically Processed Data
While using the App, some information about your device and usage patterns may be automatically processed. This data is usually non-personal, and we can only access it in an aggregated form. We process this information based on our legitimate interest in enhancing our App and providing users with the best experience. Otherwise, we may not be able to offer all the services and features of the App.
The App might employ automated processing of your personal data, including profiling. This refers to any form of automated handling of personal data that uses this information to assess certain personal aspects related to you, especially to analyze or predict factors concerning your personal preferences, interests, behavior, location, or movements.
We utilize third-party automatic data processing technologies (like Google and Facebook) to analyze specific data sent by your device or our App. These automatic data processing technologies (advertising or analytics tools) provide us with the data outlined below. We do not have control over, supervise, or are responsible for how these third parties handle your personal data. Any enquiries about the disclosure of your personal information to us should be directed to these third parties.
The data that may be processed includes:
Advertisers / Advertising ID, device brand and model, type and version of mobile web browser, IP address, MAC address and IMEI, account information (e.g., email), the make and version of the device’s operating system, locale data, MCC (Mobile Country Code) data, location and related information, cookies, and similar technologies.
The automatic processing of your data through these technologies starts when you begin using the App.
2.3 Why We Process Your Personal Data
Our primary aim is to continually refine our App and offer you fresh experiences. As part of this goal, we employ your data for the following specific purposes:
(a) Providing Our Service: We utilize information that you provide, along with automatically processed data, to deliver the services you request.
(b) Delivering Targeted Content: We may use automatically processed data for marketing purposes, such as presenting ads that align with your preferences. We offer personalized content and information, which can include online ads or other forms of marketing.
(c) Ensuring Safety and Compliance: We strive to keep our App free from spam and fraudulent content to ensure a secure and enjoyable environment. Your information may be used to prevent, detect, and investigate fraud, security breaches, potentially prohibited or illegal activities, protect our trademarks, and enforce our Terms of Use.
(d) Communicating With You: We use the information we have to engage with you via newsletters. This allows us to send you marketing notifications, gather your feedback about our App experience, and inform you about our policies and terms. We also use your information to respond when you reach out to us.
(e) Enhancing Our App: We use automatically processed data to gain insights into user behavior and trends, identify potential outages or technical issues, and operate, protect, improve, and optimize our App.
Should new reasons for processing your personal data emerge, we will notify you before initiating processing for these new purposes by updating this Privacy Statement accordingly.
III. DISCLOSURE OF YOUR INFORMATION
3.1  Third Parties Channels
We gather specific categories of your personal data, including identifiers, commercial data, internet activity, geolocation data, and inferences drawn from these categories. This data may be shared with third parties.
We guarantee that we will not lease or sell your personal data to third parties. However, we may share tools like cookies, log files, device identifiers, and location data with third-party organizations offering automatic data processing technologies for the App. We do not have control over these third parties' tracking technologies or their usage.
Third-party advertising partners may receive certain information like cookie data. This allows ad networks, among others, to deliver targeted advertisements they believe will be most relevant to you.
The App may utilize one or more of the following third-party advertising services and analytics tools: Adjust; Apple SearchAds; Facebook; Firebase; Google AdWords; TikTok; Amplitude; AppMetrica.
To learn more about these services and their privacy options, please visit their respective websites and privacy policies.
In certain circumstances, such as legal requirements, public interest, or other unexpected situations, we may need to disclose your personal data:
If mandated by law;
When we believe in good faith that disclosure is required to protect our rights, ensure your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request;
In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, you will be notified via email and/or a prominent notice on our App about any changes in ownership or uses of your personal data, as well as any choices you may have regarding your personal data.
3.2  International Data Transfer
Operating on an international scale, we offer our App to users globally.
Both ourselves and third-party entities that offer automatic data processing technologies for the App, as well as our third-party advertising partners, may transfer automatically processed data across borders - from your country or jurisdiction to other countries or jurisdictions worldwide.
If you are based in regions like the European Union, US or others with distinct data processing laws that may differ from those of England & Wales, please note that we may move information, including personal data, to a country and jurisdiction that may not offer the same data protection laws as your jurisdiction.
This implies that your personal data could be transferred to a third country, a territory, or one or more specified sectors within that third country, or an international organization where data privacy and confidentiality regulations might not offer the same level of personal data protection as your home country.
Regarding data storage, we use the services of hosting organizations. We prioritize your privacy and thus encrypt your personal data before transmitting it to the hosting organizations for storage. Please be aware that we only collaborate with hosting organizations that have passed our security and reliability assessments.
We strive to ensure that any recipient of personal data offers adequate protection for the received personal data, in compliance with current legislation governing such information. By using the App, you consent to us transferring your personal data to any third country, territory, or one or more specified sectors within that third country, or an international organization.
3.3 Duration Of Personal Data Usage
Typically, we hold onto your personal data for as long as it's required to fulfill the contract between us and to adhere to legal obligations. If you decide that you no longer want us to utilize your information that we have physical access to and store, you can request that we delete your personal data and terminate your account.
Nonetheless, certain data may continue to be stored for a specified period if the information is needed to comply with legal obligations such as taxation, accounting, auditing, or for preserving safety and data backup configurations, preventing fraud, or other malicious activities.
IV. EXERCISING YOUR RIGHTS
4.1 Data Processing
Regarding the data we hold and access, you possess the right to approach us about the following matters:
Data Access and Transferability:
You can request duplicates of your personal data that we retain.
Modification or Correction of Data:
If you're unable to amend data via your account, you have the right to request us to modify, update or rectify your data.
Processing Restriction:
Under certain circumstances, you may have the right to limit how we use your personal data.
Data Retention and Removal:
We generally keep data as long as your account is active or as needed to provide the App. However, specific retention periods can vary depending on the context of the processing we undertake and our legal obligations. You have the right to request us to erase all or part of the personal data we have on you. You can also delete your account at any time if you have one. In order to comply with our legal obligations, or where we have a legitimate interest (e.g., preventing fraud and abuse and maintaining and enhancing security), we may need to retain some of your personal data even after you have closed your account.
In some situations, you can object to the automatic processing of your personal data. If your personal data is processed for direct marketing purposes, you may request to stop processing your data for these purposes. Please contact the third-party services listed in Section IV of this Privacy Policy to learn how to object to the processing of your data. Most of them have clear guidelines on their privacy pages, functional API, or other options.
Please note that we guarantee the above rights only in relation to the information you provide.
Please note that you can opt out of marketing tracking by emailing the developer account.
4.2 Security
We place great importance on the security of your personal data. We adhere to widely accepted industry standards to safeguard the personal data provided to us, both during transmission and upon receipt.
We take reasonable and suitable measures to guard personal data from loss, misuse, and unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction, considering the risks involved in processing and the nature of the personal data.
We implement suitable technical and organizational measures aimed at implementing data-protection principles effectively, such as data minimization, and integrating necessary safeguards into the processing. We aim for your personal data to be encrypted with proper and robust encryption algorithms, including hashing where feasible.
Regrettably, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is entirely secure. We strive to protect your personal data; however, we cannot guarantee its absolute security. If your personal data is compromised due to a security breach, we will promptly notify you in accordance with applicable law.
4.3 Information Relating to Children
Our App is not designed for individuals under the age of 18. As such, we do not intentionally collect or solicit any personal data from individuals under 18. No one under the age of 18 may provide any personal data to the App. If you are under 18, refrain from using or providing any information on this App or through any of its features. Do not provide any information about yourself, including your email address. If we discover that we have collected personal data from an individual under 18 without parental consent verification, we will delete that data as quickly as possible. If you believe that we might have any data from or about an individual under 18, please contact us.
V. PRIVACY POLICY MODIFICATIONS
We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices and services. When we post changes to this Privacy Policy, we will update the date of this Privacy Policy. Continued use of the Services after such date constitutes acceptance of such updates.
VI.HOW TO CONTACT US
Should you have any questions or comments, please email: support@screen-casting.app